{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.1",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 1 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:1",
      "text": "The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:2",
      "text": "To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:3",
      "text": "To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:4",
      "text": "To give subtilty to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:5",
      "text": "A wise man will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:6",
      "text": "To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:7",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:8",
      "text": "My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:9",
      "text": "For they shall be an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:10",
      "text": "My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:11",
      "text": "If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:12",
      "text": "Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:13",
      "text": "We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:14",
      "text": "Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:15",
      "text": "My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:16",
      "text": "For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:17",
      "text": "Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:18",
      "text": "And they lay wait for their own blood; they lurk privily for their own lives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:19",
      "text": "So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:20",
      "text": "Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:21",
      "text": "She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:22",
      "text": "How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:23",
      "text": "Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:24",
      "text": "Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:25",
      "text": "But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:26",
      "text": "I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:27",
      "text": "When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh upon you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:28",
      "text": "Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:29",
      "text": "For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the Lord:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:30",
      "text": "They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:31",
      "text": "Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:32",
      "text": "For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.1.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:33",
      "text": "But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
